      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A successful mitigation of damages defense significantly weakens a breach of contract claim because it shifts the burden onto the plaintiff to prove they minimized their losses. If the defendant can show the plaintiff acted unreasonably or failed to take reasonable steps to lessen the financial harm, the damages awarded will be reduced or eliminated. This defense essentially argues that the plaintiff's inaction, rather than just the breach, caused the full extent of the claimed damages.",
